{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Situational Monologue Drill (Elevator Pitch practice)",
  "description": "Add a new speaking drill that trains longer, structured monologues for real-life situations вЂ” a gap between single-sentence drills (shadowing, stress, linkers) and full conversations. Users pick a scenario (e.g. 'Introduce yourself at a networking event вЂ” 45s', 'Explain your job to a new colleague вЂ” 30s', 'Describe a recent project in a stand-up вЂ” 60s', 'Pitch a weekend hobby вЂ” 45s', 'Tell an interviewer about a strength вЂ” 60s') and see a target duration plus a content-beat checklist (e.g. name в†’ role в†’ focus в†’ fun fact в†’ call-to-action). They record speech with the existing mic/STT flow, then submit the transcript + duration.\n\nBackend (app/routers/monologue.py + app/dal/monologue.py):\n- GET /api/monologue/scenarios в†’ returns a curated static list of ~8 scenarios with id, title, prompt, target_seconds, content_beats[].\n- POST /api/monologue/attempt { scenario_id, transcript, duration_seconds } в†’ calls LLM (copilot_client) with a strict JSON prompt to evaluate: beats_covered[] (which checklist items were addressed), fluency_score 0-100 (uses wpm + filler ratio computed server-side using existing filler-word list), structure_score 0-100, overall_score 0-100, one_line_feedback, suggested_rewrite_opening. Persists row and returns feedback.\n- GET /api/monologue/history?scenario_id=... в†’ last 20 attempts + personal best (highest overall_score) per scenario.\n\nSchema: add new table via CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS in app/database.py SCHEMA. Since this is a brand-new table (never existed before), no _MIGRATIONS ALTER entries are required:\n\n  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS monologue_attempts (\n    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    scenario_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n    transcript TEXT NOT NULL,\n    duration_seconds REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    word_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    filler_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    wpm REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    coverage_ratio REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    fluency_score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    structure_score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    overall_score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    feedback_json TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n    created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n  );\n  CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_monologue_attempts_created ON monologue_attempts(created_at DESC);\n  CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_monologue_attempts_scenario ON monologue_attempts(scenario_id);\n\nFrontend (frontend/src/pages/MonologueDrill.tsx + route entry in App.tsx/navigation): scenario picker cards with target duration chips; practice view shows prompt, live countdown timer that turns amber near target, existing mic recorder, and a content-beat checklist that lights up (вњ“/вњ—) after submission based on beats_covered; results panel shows donut for coverage %, sparkline of prior overall_scores, wpm + filler metrics, and the suggested opener rewrite with a 'try again' button. Also surface a 'Monologue' tile on Home under speaking drills.\n\nWhy this complements the app: recent iterations focus on micro-skills (one sentence, one contrast, one word). Learners specifically need to practice producing a coherent 30вЂ“60s structured stretch вЂ” the exact thing that appears in interviews, intros, and stand-ups вЂ” and no current drill covers this macro-level speaking structure.",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/database.py", "app/routers/monologue.py", "app/dal/monologue.py", "app/main.py", "frontend/src/pages/MonologueDrill.tsx"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
